============================================================
  DISEASES & MEDICINE
============================================================

Disease:     Cholera
Type:        Bacterial
Pathogen:    Vibrio cholerae
Transmission:Contaminated water
Symptoms:    Profuse watery diarrhea, vomiting
Treatment:   Oral rehydration, antibiotics
Deaths/yr:   0.095M
Vaccine:     Yes
Discovered:  1854

Disease:     Tuberculosis
Type:        Bacterial
Pathogen:    M. tuberculosis
Transmission:Airborne droplets
Symptoms:    Persistent cough, night sweats
Treatment:   6-9 month antibiotics
Deaths/yr:   1.6M
Vaccine:     Yes (BCG, partial)
Discovered:  1882

Disease:     Cardiovascular Disease
Type:        Metabolic
Pathogen:    Non-communicable
Transmission:Non-communicable
Symptoms:    Chest pain, shortness of breath
Treatment:   Statins, surgery, stents
Deaths/yr:   17.9M
Vaccine:     No (for most types)
Discovered:  Ancient

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Nash Equilibrium
Branch:       Game Theory
Formula:      No player benefits from unilateral strategy change
Applications: Economics, AI, political science
Discoverer:   John Nash (1950)

Theorem/Law:  Euler Polyhedron Formula
Branch:       Topology
Formula:      V - E + F = 2
Applications: Architecture, crystallography
Discoverer:   Leonhard Euler (1758)

Theorem/Law:  Bayes Theorem
Branch:       Probability
Formula:      P(H|E) = P(E|H)P(H)/P(E)
Applications: ML, spam filters, medical testing
Discoverer:   Thomas Bayes (1763)

